>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The bank is apparently a former tramway but there is no mention of it in the usual reference sources.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="tin-adit">Tin Adit
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://dartmoorwalking.org/p/meldon-and-the-west-okemont-valley/5.jpg"
width="1600"
height="900"
srcset="https://dartmoorwalking.org/p/meldon-and-the-west-okemont-valley/5_hu_f856a7b75f2e866b.jpg 480w, https://dartmoorwalking.org/p/meldon-and-the-west-okemont-valley/5_hu_c5af5fab8c7a4592.jpg 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Adit at SX 56375 92020"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="177"
data-flex-basis="426px"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The staining on the ground by metalliferous leaching indicates that there are metal ores in this vicinity. This particular mine was dug for Tin.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Adits are horizontal tunnels used in mining. Some are used for access in and out and some are used for draining upper levels of water. This one is only open for about 10 meters, and was worked in tandem with the shafts on the slope immediately above it.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>There would have been a spoil heap here when they were dug, but that has been removed by later activity.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://dartmoorwalking.org/p/meldon-and-the-west-okemont-valley/6.jpg"
width="1600"
height="900"
srcset="https://dartmoorwalking.org/p/meldon-and-the-west-okemont-valley/6_hu_343fd753169ea962.jpg 480w, https://dartmoorwalking.org/p/meldon-and-the-west-okemont-valley/6_hu_47557f2cc0bf3972.jpg 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Internal view of the adit"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="177"
data-flex-basis="426px"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>&lt;a class="link" href="https://www.heritagegateway.org.uk/Gateway/Results_Single.aspx?uid=MDV120318&amp;amp;resourceID=104" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>Heritage Gateway MDV120318 - Adit west of the West Okement River at Meldon Quarry &lt;/a>&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;a class="link" href="https://www.heritagegateway.org.uk/Gateway/Results_Single.aspx?uid=MDV120320&amp;amp;resourceID=104" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
