&lt;h2 id="meldon-dam">Meldon Dam
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://dartmoorwalking.org/p/meldon-and-the-west-okemont-valley/52.jpg"
width="1600"
height="900"
srcset="https://dartmoorwalking.org/p/meldon-and-the-west-okemont-valley/52_hu_13d8a0432435bd91.jpg 480w, https://dartmoorwalking.org/p/meldon-and-the-west-okemont-valley/52_hu_f263c03cecbbe152.jpg 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="The path to Meldon Dam"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="177"
data-flex-basis="426px"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://dartmoorwalking.org/p/meldon-and-the-west-okemont-valley/53.jpg"
width="1600"
height="900"
srcset="https://dartmoorwalking.org/p/meldon-and-the-west-okemont-valley/53_hu_881d19bfaa2e695e.jpg 480w, https://dartmoorwalking.org/p/meldon-and-the-west-okemont-valley/53_hu_6b02ce58c6197590.jpg 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="A last look back at the Viaduct"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="177"
data-flex-basis="426px"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://dartmoorwalking.org/p/meldon-and-the-west-okemont-valley/55.jpg"
width="1600"
height="899"
srcset="https://dartmoorwalking.org/p/meldon-and-the-west-okemont-valley/55_hu_69a66581f684e60c.jpg 480w, https://dartmoorwalking.org/p/meldon-and-the-west-okemont-valley/55_hu_8cd4714d3ed2e014.jpg 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Across the dam"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="177"
data-flex-basis="427px"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>Meldon Dam was begun in 1970 and completed in 1974, making it the newest of Dartmoor&amp;rsquo;s large dams.&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>It is 55 meters (180 feet) high.&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>It&amp;rsquo;s 200 meters (660 feet) wide.&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>The reservoir is stocked with Brown Trout for licenced angling.&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>Uniquely, Meldon reservoir became the first water-supply body to produce electricity when a 500kW turbine generator was installed in 1987 to produce electricity to work the pumps and treatment works.&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>&lt;a class="link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meldon_Reservoir" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>Wikipedia - Meldon Dam&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://dartmoorwalking.org/p/meldon-and-the-west-okemont-valley/56.jpg"
width="5179"
height="2913"
srcset="https://dartmoorwalking.org/p/meldon-and-the-west-okemont-valley/56_hu_482f72f3cea46773.jpg 480w, https://dartmoorwalking.org/p/meldon-and-the-west-okemont-valley/56_hu_48f8e34121b583cf.jpg 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Surveyors’ Theodolite Platform"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="177"
data-flex-basis="426px"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>At each end of the dam are these structures. They are used to check the dam&amp;rsquo;s alignment and curvature to ensure there is no movement.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://dartmoorwalking.org/p/meldon-and-the-west-okemont-valley/57.jpg"
width="5184"
height="2916"
srcset="https://dartmoorwalking.org/p/meldon-and-the-west-okemont-valley/57_hu_85cf8654fd1bd035.jpg 480w, https://dartmoorwalking.org/p/meldon-and-the-west-okemont-valley/57_hu_6f88f2d03a8d7aac.jpg 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="View from the pillar"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="177"
data-flex-basis="426px"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://dartmoorwalking.org/p/meldon-and-the-west-okemont-valley/58.jpg"
width="5184"
height="2916"
srcset="https://dartmoorwalking.org/p/meldon-and-the-west-okemont-valley/58_hu_3a06a5ac4715c63.jpg 480w, https://dartmoorwalking.org/p/meldon-and-the-west-okemont-valley/58_hu_5c7c8ed6dc59c72c.jpg 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="View across the reservoir from the dam"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="177"
data-flex-basis="426px"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://dartmoorwalking.org/p/meldon-and-the-west-okemont-valley/54.jpg"
width="1600"
height="900"
srcset="https://dartmoorwalking.org/p/meldon-and-the-west-okemont-valley/54_hu_482226ab9ce0399b.jpg 480w, https://dartmoorwalking.org/p/meldon-and-the-west-okemont-valley/54_hu_8d52610ddee8a085.jpg 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="The system for the spillway to control overflow when the dam is full"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="177"
data-flex-basis="426px"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>This spillway appears to be a combination of a straight chute and stepped spillway features. These are designed to reduce the kinetic energy of overflowing water and thereby reduce erosion damage. This system is essentially an uncontrolled system in that there are no mechanical gates or vanes to regulate the rate of overflow at the top of the dam.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://dartmoorwalking.org/p/meldon-and-the-west-okemont-valley/59.jpg"
width="1600"
height="900"
srcset="https://dartmoorwalking.org/p/meldon-and-the-west-okemont-valley/59_hu_2b785ef1d07988b.jpg 480w, https://dartmoorwalking.org/p/meldon-and-the-west-okemont-valley/59_hu_77a1976cfbed2e6.jpg 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Commemorative plaque"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="177"
data-flex-basis="426px"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Many of these plaques on Dartmoor&amp;rsquo;s reservoirs were made of bronze and have been stolen in recent years for their scrap value. Hopefully this one does not appear to the thieves.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;em>Once across the dam, we are back at the car park and our walk is complete&lt;/em>&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="parking">Parking
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>Parking is at the Meldon Reservoir site, which is Pay and Display. It also has toilet facilities and an electric car charging point.&lt;/p>
